main event: Three college professors observed an unidentified object in Potomac, Maryland on July 29, 1963.
interesting points: The object was described as slightly brighter than stars, extremely slow moving, and round in shape, with an estimated size of 1.5 to 2 degrees of arc per minute.
The observers' conclusion was that there was insufficient data to evaluate the nature of the observed object.
The Air Force investigated the sighting and suggested it may have been a research balloon that was launched from Wallops Island, Virginia and tracked towards the Potomac area.
The Air Force could not positively confirm the object as the research balloon, but stated that the description and timing of the sighting suggested it as a possible cause.
The Air Force provided additional information about their atmospheric research program involving the release of instrument packages carried by balloons.
